This paper deals with the application of conditional generative adversarial networks (GANs) for stain-style transfer in histopathological images. This involves image processing and computer vision techniques, which are typically covered in the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of GANs for image generation and transfer is a popular topic in the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also involves the use of feature-preserving loss, which is a technique used in image retrieval (cs.IR) and multimedia (cs.MM) research.
